Package: mismeasured
Type: Package
Title: SIMEX and MC-SIMEX Correction for Measurement Error and Misclassification
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Maciej", "Beresewicz", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "maciej.beresewicz@ue.poznan.pl",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8281-4301")),
    person("Helmut", "Kuechenhoff", role = "ctb"))
Description: High-performance implementation of the Simulation-Extrapolation (SIMEX)
    and Misclassification SIMEX (MC-SIMEX) algorithms for correcting measurement error
    and misclassification bias in regression models. The simulation step uses compiled
    C++ code via 'Rcpp' and 'RcppEigen' for Iteratively Reweighted Least Squares (IRLS)
    fitting, providing substantial speedups over pure-R implementations. Supports
    Gaussian, Poisson, and Binomial GLM families with a formula interface mimicking
    'glm()' and standard S3 methods. Based on Cook and Stefanski (1994)
    <doi:10.1080/01621459.1994.10476871> and Kuechenhoff, Mwalili, and Lesaffre (2006)
    <doi:10.1111/j.1541-0420.2005.00396.x>.
License: GPL (>= 3)
